# Service & Infrastructure

**Long-running operations:** If something takes more than a minute, run in background. Check periodically. Mark done only when actually finished.

**Port conflicts:** Kill the process using the port before starting a new one. Verify port is free before proceeding.

**External services:** Use proper CLI tools and APIs (`gh`, cloud CLIs). Don't scrape web UIs when APIs exist.

**Background jobs:** Don't block on completion indefinitely. Use bounded polling or notifications.

When starting dev servers, prefer known project scripts from `package.json` over ad-hoc commands.
